status_message:
DAY AFTER UPDATE - WE STOOD BY OUR CALL

Friends, 

Last night we called the race a good two hours before the "networks" here on the page and at our HQ over at LibertyNEWS. Our breaking news alert, giving Donald Trump the win, was met with some very harsh and skeptical comments here in the page. 

From the "you guys are idiots" to the "I trust the media and will wait for their official call" type of comments... we saw it all. And quite frankly, we were quite taken aback by it. 

Look, we get that it was a big call to make. We didn't at all take it lightly. Not one bit. But here's the thing. We're not just some blog. We have a full time staff. We have offices here in Wisconsin. We have TV and audio studios. 

We are media. 

No, we don't have hundred million dollar budgets and New York offices. But we're just as credible as the "networks," and in many cases far more credible. 

At some point America is going to have to diminish the line between what we traditionally view as "media" vs what we view as "alternative media."

The networks have lied to you. Period. 

They used their obviously and blatantly false polls to try and depress the vote against Hillary. They refuse to investigate the truth behind the most corrupt Washington in our history. Yeah, they'll report on a press conference. But they won't go in and expose the fact that a majority of our government/representation is bought and paid for. 

How can we in one breath scream at a dishonest media for betraying us on the truth and the next claim we trust that very media?

We called the race earlier because our very talented team was confident in what we were tracking in Pennsylvania. Our team had been watching ten counties in Florida and ten counties in Pennsylvania all night. These counties were absolutely make or break. 

We knew it. And when we saw that Clinton had no path to outpace Trump in PA, we called PA for Trump. 

We're not upset that some were skeptical. We encourage that. Heck, we're skeptical about everything! 

But we were a little offended that some called for "official" numbers from "media."

Again, LibertyNEWS is a real business. With real offices, real staff and a real goal to bring you news most major networks won't bring you. This because we're sick and tired of relying on a completely dishonest media. 

We strongly stand by the notion that you should trust but verify. That should ALWAYS be the case. But we also ask that Americans stop trusting the networks the we have for so many years. Even when we "say" we don't. 

The networks are not your friend. They all worked against you this year. They aren't telling you the truth about the economy, the middle east and many, many more critically important issues. 

We are. 

And last night when we called the race long before the networks, we were telling you the truth then as well. 

A huge thanks goes out to our team in both our Kenosha and Virginia offices. It was a long night and we were exhausted when we finally shut down at 3:30 am. 

And thank you to our readers, our Facebook fans and those who comment, like and share our content. Your engagement with what we post is a huge part of what makes it all possible. 

Thank you, 

Eric Odom
Managing Director, LibertyNEWS

CANDIDATE ENDORSEMENT TIME

First off, we want to thank each and every one of you for helping keep our page one of the largest and most active liberty minded pages on Facebook! With nearly a million and a half fans/likes and 1,000+ new likes added per week we are, without question, a top freedom advocate on Facebook. 

Second, we want to say that our candidate endorsement decision is not made lightly. Nor is it an endorsement we make to try and force you to come to the same conclusion. We hope you'll all respect that this is simply our opinion. If you disagree that's fine and we fully respect your position. 

Third, we want to state up front that our staff were ALL in the corner of a candidate other than Donald Trump in the primary. We're very familiar with the concerns on Trump and we very much share many of those concerns. 

It should also be known that several of our staff have voted third party in the past and we do not at all pull the lever based on party. In fact, it's our belief the two party system has corrupted our government and caused significant damage to our Republic. 

Fourth, we do not make this endorsement under the explanation of the "lesser of two evils" argument that is often prominent across social media. For us this isn't about the lesser of two evils. A scenario that existed for us when it came to John McCain and Mitt Romney (Some of our staff voted third party in both of those elections). 

For us this is about buying time with the bonus of a certain reality that if Donald Trump actually does some of what he promises we will be better off for it. For us this is about extending preservation of our great nation, avoiding world war for a bit longer and living to fight another day. 

If Hillary Clinton is elected we believe the following will happen. 

- War with Russia will quickly become a reality (Clinton consistently calls for a no-fly zone in Syria, an act that will assuredly result in Russia engaging the U.S. in full on war)

- The Supreme Court will be a new legislative body for Anti-American policy for decades to come. 

- Our healthcare system will be dealt a final death blow and forced into single payer. 

- TPP will be signed, sending what is left of our economy into its grave. 

- Taxes will skyrocket to levels we can't even fathom. 

- Clinton will further corrupt our federal agencies, creating a federal government that is fully rogue and acting outside any sensible level of control by We The People.

Among many, many other terrible realities that will rip the foundation of our nation apart at the seams. 

We believe our founding fathers often had to make decisions they would prefer not make with the understanding that they were playing a strategic chess like situation on a game board that had its pieces stacked against them. 

We believe that if Hillary Clinton is elected we as a nation will not live to fight another day. And that's a risk we're simply not willing to take. We will not gamble with our nation as the collateral. 

Our staff will be voting for Donald Trump here in Wisconsin next Tuesday. 

-The LibertyNEWS Team
